{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab The All India Medical Conference took definite action in \softline
placing the subject of birth control where it belongs, as part of \softline
the physicians program for preserving the health of his nation.   \softline
It passed a resolution recommending that instruction in \softline
conception control methods should form part of the curriculum in \softline
medical colleges and schools and in the training of health \softline
visitors, nurses and midwives.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab I also lectured and showed scientific films which I had with \softline
me on the Biology of Conception, at the All Indian Obstetric and \softline
Gynecological Congress, the first of its kind in India.  Indeed \softline
the movement got off to a good start in India, having the support \softline
of organized medicine, and of individual doctors everywhere.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab One of the highlights of my stay in India was my visit to 
Mahatma Gandhi, and two memorable conversations I had with him.  \softline
Gandhi has aroused the men and women of India as no one else has \softline
done, and the women of India wanted me to se him.  He turned out \softline
to be even a better feminist than I am.  For I believe that \softline
parenthood and marriage should be put on a fifty-fifty basis, \softline
that the man as well as the woman should have something to say \softline
about how many children should be brought into the world.  But \softline
Gandhi would leave all this to the women.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab Mr. Gandhi and I disagreed with mutual tolerance, and I am \softline
glad to say, respect.  {\u8220\'93}I think highly of your purpose,{\u8221\'94} he said \softline
to me in parting. {\u8220\'93}May God guide you right.{\u8221\'94}\par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab By the time I left India, fifty teaching centers had been \softline
established, and supplies had been distributed to public health \softline
officials and hospitals. My plan on leaving India in the same as \softline
I make here in America: Those in authority, those in charge of \softline
public health, those advocating the cause of social and mental \softline
health should take a firm stand and include birth control \softline
knowledge and its practice where it is desired and needed.  This \softline
is a responsibility that can no longer be evaded or shirked, and \softline
one which the masses have a right to expect. \par
}\pard \fs24\sl480\slmult1\tx720\tqr\tx9450 
